A lot of recommended #zerowaste behaviors are also ones I find too difficult or unachievable for people.

And others are just plain consumerism...

#Zerowaste is never zero. Just because you don't see it doesn't mean it didn't exist.

One of the reasons I find trash jars misleading.

That is not the sum of your impact.

Your impact isn't dictated by your morals, often it's circumstances, not whether you instapot your yogurt.
